question.title: following warning: APT_CombinedOperatorController,0: Conversion error while calling the date_from_ustring conversion routine. Data may have been lost
question.body:
Good morning everyone, I'm currently receiving the following warning in IBM Datastage: APT_CombinedOperatorController,0: Conversion error while calling the date_from_ustring conversion routine. Data may have been lost.

I'm not bringing in any date values ​​from any source; I'm just creating some current date fields in a transformer: fechacarga(CurrentDate) and fechahora(CurrentTimestamp).

What could be the cause of this warning?

question_comments.body: 1) What has this to do with Postgres? 2) If Postgres is involved what is the actual code being run that causes the issue?
